      "created_at": "2024-07-08T07:13:22.323Z",
      "cooked": "<p>Sorry for the delayed response.  I am on vacation and responding slowly to non-emergencies.  The rules are fairly complex, it\u2019s generally taking the last 10 second average and adjusting the target every 30 seconds, I think it lowers the target if it is 2% greater than the target and it increases rather slowly but I don\u2019t remember the exact rules.  If you want to control the warmup or want a rapid change then switching to ERG mode is the best way.  If you are in ERG mode at 200w for 30 seconds and then switch to HR mode it will start at 200w and adjust from there.</p>\n<p>Hope that helps.</p>",
